        "subject": "LU-17083 socklnd: Skip conn close on simulated error",
        "message": "LU-17083 socklnd: Skip conn close on simulated error\n\nIt seems socklnd can be slow to re-establish connections following an\nerror which can result in failures for subsequent tests. Skip the\nconnection close when we're simulating errors.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: testlist=sanity-lnet env=ONLY=205,ONLY_REPEAT=100\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <chris.horn@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: I57942946f94d503cf144fc77f566878c421f06d2\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60850\nReviewed-by: Frank Sehr <fsehr@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Serguei Smirnov <ssmirnov@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
